name: Big Jimmy #1
description: Jimmy is a 14 year old Martian boy. He's shy and lonely but somehow he finds himself representing Mars in the Triumph Of The Solar System, a galaxy wide battle tournament. Without so much as an explanation or a training montage, Jimmy is thrown in the deep end and must avoid getting his little blue face punched off while meets new friends and enemies and searches for the truth about why nobody will tell him the truth about why he has to keep fighting monsters. See a preview here! 36 pages. B&W. Signed & Numbered 1st edition.

name: Big Jimmy #2
description: Jimmy, Cheezdood and Candyhead are back in two hilarious tales of violence and chuckles. In the first story, Jimmy continues his accidental adventure through the world of deadly battle tournaments, coming up against a foe much stronger and monstrous than him. Can his parents give him the confidence he needs to win the day? Then in story two, Candyhead and Cheezdood go on a babe hunt, with DEADLY CONSEQUENCES! See a preview here! 28 pages. B&W. Signed.

name: Now We Are Running...
description: "Gratuitous swearing is NEVER funny" - James's Dad. 'Now We Are Running...' is my first full comic book with words and pictures by me! It's a collection of pop culture spoofs n' goofs with a little bad language and violence thrown in because I think it's big and clever. Inside! Meet Steven and George, two young-buck, hot-shot directors with Hollywood dreams in their eyes. Finally, learn the sordid (and almost sort of maybe true) stories behind some of Spielberg's greatest films! Plus! Discover the legend of the Vangrooover Brothers, three body-building triplets from a German muscle-family who undergo a heroic metamorphosis and then go on adventures with fighting and explosions and that! See a preview here. 28 pages. Signed. Paper. Also staples.

name: Jurassic Dorks: The A to Z of the Eighties Art Book
description: Featuring 26 amazing pieces of artwork by Mark Pearce, Jessica Bradley, John-Paul Bove, Dylan Cook and James Stayte. This art book features all of the pieces displayed in our exhibition, held in Bristol, Christmas 2011. From A for Arnold Schwarzenegger to Z for Zelda, enjoy the 1980's the alphabetical way! (For a preview of the book click here ) All books are signed by the artists (and some have awesome doodles!)
